SIMPLE: etherealize
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Etherealize
<hw>E*the"re*al*ize</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>To convert into ether, or into subtile fluid; to saturate with
ether.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To render ethereal or spiritlike.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q><qex>Etherealized</qex>, moreover, by spiritual communications
with the other world.</q> <rj><qau>Hawthorne.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Ethereally</ent>⟦br⟧
